### The two `EKF2_GPS_CTRL` branches

- **`EKF2_GPS_CTRL = 1` (HPOS only):** `controlGnssHeightFusion` runs every cycle, but the gate
  `(_params.gnss_ctrl & GnssCtrl::VPOS)` at `gnss_height_control.cpp:89` is **false**. The
  `continuing_conditions_passing` / `starting_conditions_passing` are false, so the `gps_hgt`
  control flag never turns on, `_gps_hgt_b_est` never goes active, and the GPS height bias `fuseBias`
  at `:85` is also effectively gated (and even if reached, the bias estimator is inactive). Net: **GPS
  does not affect height at all**; only horizontal GPS (`controlGpsFusion`) runs.
- **`VPOS` bit set (`2 / 3 / 7`):** the gate passes. On the first pass `starting_conditions_passing`
  is true and, because `HGT_REF != GNSS`, the **non-reference** start branch runs
  (`:149-151`): it only initializes the GPS bias (`setBias(pos(2) + meas)`) and sets the fusion active
  — it does **not** reset the vertical state. From then on GPS height fuses into the state (`:105`)
  with its bias subtracted, and the GPS height bias is continuously estimated (`:85`).

