## 6. Bias-estimation equations

Single-state scalar Kalman filter, `src/modules/ekf2/EKF/bias_estimator.cpp:42-145`. The bias state
`b` is the offset (in metres) between a non-reference height source and the EKF vertical-position
state; `P_b` is its variance.

### Sign convention

Height measurements (baro, GPS-MSL) are **positive up**; the EKF state `pos(2)` is **positive down**
(NED). Hence:

```
vertical innovation fed to the EKF :  innov = -(measurement - b)
bias "measurement" fed to estimator:  z = measurement - (-pos(2)) = measurement + pos(2)
```

(baro: `baro_height_control.cpp:79` & `:106`; GPS: `gnss_height_control.cpp:72` & `:85`.)

### Predict (`bias_estimator.cpp:42-63`)

The bias is modelled as constant (random walk in covariance only):

```
b      ← b                          (state held constant)
P_b    ← P_b + Q · dt               Q = _process_psd  (baro_bias_nsd² / gps_hgt_bias_nsd², via setProcessNoiseSpectralDensity)
```

If `isOffsetDetected()` is true, `Q·dt` is multiplied by `_process_var_boost_gain` to let the bias
catch up faster. `P_b` is then constrained to `[1e-8, _state_var_max]` (`constrainStateVar`).

### Fuse (`bias_estimator.cpp:70-86`)

```
S  = P_b + max(0.01², R)            innovation variance        (:72)   R = measurement_var
r  = z - b                          innovation                 (:73)
K  = P_b / S                        Kalman gain                (:74)
test_ratio = r² / (gate² · S)                                  (:90)   gate = _gate_size

if (test_ratio < 1):                                           (:77,95)
    b   ← b + K · r                 state update               (:100)
    P_b ← P_b - K · P_b             covariance update          (:105, then constrain)
```

### Vertical-position fusion into the 24-state EKF (`vel_pos_fusion.cpp`)

The bias-corrected innovation and its variance go to the main filter on the down-position state
(index 9):

```
aid_src.innovation          = -(measurement - b)
aid_src.innovation_variance = measurement_var + P_b           (baro :80 / GPS :73)

K_row = P(row, 9) / innov_var       for each state row
P    -= KHP
fuse(K, innov)                      apply state correction
```

`P(9,9)` is the vertical-position variance. Note the source variance handed to the main filter is
inflated by the bias variance `P_b`, so an uncertain bias makes that source less trusted.

### Offset detection (`bias_estimator.cpp:109-131`)

A low-pass filter of the *signed* test ratio plus same-sign innovation timers flags a persistent
offset:

```
isOffsetDetected = |LPF(sign(r)·test_ratio)| > 0.2
                 OR  time_since_last_positive_innov > τ
                 OR  time_since_last_negative_innov > τ
```

which triggers the process-noise boost in `predict()` above.

### State vector reference (`common.h` `stateSample`)

| Index | State            |
|-------|------------------|
| 0–3   | quaternion (attitude) |
| 4–6   | NED velocity     |
| 7–9   | NED position (`pos(2)` = down, **index 9**) |
| 10–12 | gyro bias        |
| 13–15 | accel bias       |
| 16–18 | earth mag field  |
| 19–21 | body mag bias    |
| 22–23 | horizontal wind  |

